<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
After studying Maurice 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pic’s">Pic's</normalizedToken>
collection at the MNHN, we found that the holotype 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">P. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of examined had all the diagnostic traits of 
<taxonomicName genus="Me." lsidName="Me. ciceroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="ciceroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Me. ciceroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., antenna with 10 antennomeres, apical antennomere subdivided, labial palp with one palpomere; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3640.1.6" author="Silveira, LFL" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="79 - 87" refId="B24" refString="Silveira, LFL, Mermudes, JR, 2013. Memoan ciceroi gen. et sp. n., a remarkable new firefly genus and species from the Atlantic Rainforest (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Zootaxa 3640 (1): 79 - 87, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3640.1.6" title="Memoan ciceroi gen. et sp. n., a remarkable new firefly genus and species from the Atlantic Rainforest (Coleoptera: Lampyridae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3640.1.6" volume="3640" year="2013">Silveira and Mermudes 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we propose that 
<taxonomicName genus="Me." lsidName="Me. ciceroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="ciceroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Me. ciceroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">P. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1942.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" refId="B21" refString="Pic, M, 1942. Opuscula martialis. Revue linneanne (4): 16." title="Opuscula martialis. Revue linneanne (4): 16." year="1942">Pic (1942</bibRefCitation>
: 16) described 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">P. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">angustatus et elongatus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">testaceus. Long. 6 m</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Bresil" lsidName="Bresil" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Bresil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, - 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
Character par sa coloration claire jointe 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
sa forme 
<normalizedToken originalValue="élancée">elancee</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;. The current definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Photinus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Photinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is controversial, as pointed out by several firefly specialists (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, FA" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 72" refId="B11" refString="McDermott, FA, 1964. The taxonomy of the Lampyridae (Coleoptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 90 (1): 1 - 72" title="The taxonomy of the Lampyridae (Coleoptera)." volume="90" year="1964">McDermott 1964</bibRefCitation>
), and needs taxonomic revision. In fact, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">P. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have characters normally found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Photinus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Photinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as simple antennae shorter than 1/2 body length, pronotum with sides white and laterally expanded, abdominal tergites rounded, and phallobase relatively long (
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, FA" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 72" refId="B11" refString="McDermott, FA, 1964. The taxonomy of the Lampyridae (Coleoptera). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 90 (1): 1 - 72" title="The taxonomy of the Lampyridae (Coleoptera)." volume="90" year="1964">McDermott 1964</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we transfer 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">P. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silveira &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Memoan" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Memoan" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Memoan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, generating 
<taxonomicName genus="Me." lsidName="Me. fruhstorferi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="fruhstorferi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Me. fruhstorferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pic, 1942) comb. nov. and synonymize it with 
<taxonomicName genus="Me." lsidName="Me. ciceroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="ciceroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Me. ciceroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, syn. nov., over which it has priority.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
